Daud Olatunji,Abeokuta The Ogun State Government on Wednesday said it had approved the immediate commencement of work on the 4.65km Akute-Denro-Ishasi road bordering Lagos State. The government also said it planned to reconstruct some other roads such as the 2.3km Olusegun-Osoba-Twiney Street in Ifo Local Government Area and the 2.3km six-lane Molipa Expressway, which connects Ejinrin-Folagbade at Ijebu-Ode and Ago-Iwoye road in the Ogun East Senatorial District. The government said this through a statement issued by Chief Press Secretary to the Governor, Kunle Somorin. The statement added that the government had given approval for the immediate commencement of construction work on the three roads spread across the Ogun Central and East Senatorial districts of the state. Copyright PUNCH.
